Feature: HomeVC trending movies carousel with swipe-down list transform (UIKit)

Overview
- Add a Home screen trending section in `HomeVC` using UIKit components only.
- Data source: `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies`.
- Initial presentation: horizontal carousel with the first 5 movies from response.
- Interaction: swipe down on the trending section transforms carousel into a vertical list.
- List mode shows movie description text clamped to maximum 3 lines.

Scope
- In scope: `HomeVC` UI/interaction, endpoint integration, loading/error/empty states, UIKit-only implementation.
- Out of scope: SwiftUI view migration, backend contract changes, new endpoint creation.

Functional requirements

REQ-HVC-TM-1 Endpoint usage
- HomeVC must call `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies` on initial load.
- Query params:
  - `limit=5`
  - `days` optional; if omitted, backend default applies.
- Parsing root key: `trendingMovies`.

REQ-HVC-TM-2 Data model mapping
- Map each item fields:
  - `movieId`
  - `name`
  - `thumbnail_picture`
  - `large_picture`
  - `bookedTickets`
  - `lastBookingTime`
- If image fields are empty, UI must use local placeholder image.

REQ-HVC-TM-3 Carousel mode (default)
- Initial mode is carousel.
- Display max 5 movies in horizontal scroll.
- Each card shows at minimum:
  - poster image using an available endpoint image path (`thumbnail_picture` and/or `large_picture`)
  - movie title
- Carousel must be embeddable inside existing `HomeVC` layout without blocking other sections.

REQ-HVC-TM-4 Swipe-down transform
- A downward swipe gesture on the trending section switches to list mode.
- Transition must be animated (content transform/fade) and preserve fetched data.
- No additional network call is required for transform-only state change.

REQ-HVC-TM-5 List mode
- List mode displays the same movie set currently in carousel scope (max 5).
- Each row includes:
  - poster thumbnail
  - movie title
  - movie description text (if available), clamped to 3 lines maximum
- If description is unavailable from endpoint payload, use fallback descriptive text.

REQ-HVC-TM-6 Optional return to carousel
- Implementation may provide return-to-carousel interaction (e.g., swipe up or toggle icon), but it must not conflict with scroll behavior.

REQ-HVC-TM-7 Empty and error states
- If endpoint returns empty array, hide carousel/list cards and show compact empty-state copy.
- If request fails, show non-blocking error state and keep HomeVC usable.
- Retry behavior may be tap-to-retry on status copy, pull-to-refresh, or explicit retry control.

REQ-HVC-TM-8 UIKit-only constraint
- Must use UIKit (`UIViewController`, `UICollectionView`, `UITableView`, `UIGestureRecognizer`, Auto Layout).
- Do not use SwiftUI (`View`, `@State`, `UIHostingController`) in this feature.

REQ-HVC-TM-9 Logging and diagnostics
- Log debug info for request start/end and resulting item count.
- Do not log sensitive headers or auth tokens.

REQ-HVC-TM-10 HomeVC visual style polish
- Home screen (`HomeVC`) visual language for this feature area should follow a black/white/grey palette for a cleaner and neater look.
- Allow optional spacing/padding refinements around trending cards/rows and section containers to improve visual rhythm.
- Allow optional soft shadow styling on cards/containers to improve depth and separation without heavy contrast.
- Styling must remain UIKit-based and consistent with existing app readability/accessibility constraints.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-HVC-TM-NF-1 Responsiveness
- Trending section should render placeholder/skeleton promptly while loading.
- Mode transform animation should target smooth interaction on modern iPhones.

REQ-HVC-TM-NF-2 Accessibility
- Cards and rows must expose accessibility labels (movie title + ranking position).
- List text supports Dynamic Type where existing HomeVC typography policy allows.

REQ-HVC-TM-NF-3 Determinism
- Display order must follow backend returned order and remain stable between carousel and list modes.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] HomeVC requests trending endpoint and renders at most first 5 movies.
- [ ] Default UI is carousel mode.
- [ ] Swipe down transforms carousel into list mode with animation.
- [ ] List rows show description text with max 3 lines.
- [ ] Empty and error states are visible and non-blocking.
- [ ] Implementation uses UIKit only (no SwiftUI usage).
- [ ] HomeVC trending section follows black/white/grey style with optional padding/shadow polish.
- [ ] Prototype HTML/SVG is attached for review.

Reference files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/HomeVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/APIClient.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/BackendServices.swift`
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/homevc-trending-carousel.prototype.html`

